gnome-network-displays (0.99.0.2-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Initial PPA release of this downstream fork of upstream master, carrying:
    - libadwaita requirement lowered to 1.5.0 (builds on this release)
    - Chromecast: probe a supported VAAPI rate-control instead of hardcoding CBR
    - PulseAudio: lock the threaded mainloop; guard NULL pulse on teardown
    - Wi-Fi Display: drop the unavailable vaapipostproc and probe rate-control
    - A "disable QoS throttling" option (GSettings + Preferences switch)

 -- Pavel Řezníček <pavel.reznicek@evangnet.cz>  Fri, 29 May 2026 15:28:23 +0200

gnome-network-displays (0.99.0.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add a "disable QoS throttling" option (GSettings key disable-qos plus a
    Preferences switch) to keep a full-rate Wi-Fi Display stream flowing for
    receivers whose decoder freezes when the stream is throttled.

 -- Pavel Řezníček <cigydd@gmail.com>  Fri, 29 May 2026 14:20:31 +0200

gnome-network-displays (0.99.0.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix the Wi-Fi Display VAAPI encoder path: drop the unavailable
    vaapipostproc (vaapih264enc uploads frames itself) and probe for a
    supported rate-control instead of hardcoding CBR, mirroring the earlier
    Chromecast fix. Fixes "Error." when connecting to Miracast/WFD sinks on
    CQP-only VA drivers.

 -- Pavel Řezníček <cigydd@gmail.com>  Thu, 28 May 2026 13:36:39 +0200

gnome-network-displays (0.99.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Local build of upstream master with downstream fixes:
    - Lower the libadwaita requirement to 1.5.0 so it builds on this distro.
    - Probe for a supported VAAPI rate-control instead of hardcoding CBR.
    - Lock the PulseAudio threaded mainloop and guard NULL pulse on teardown.

 -- Pavel Řezníček <cigydd@gmail.com>  Thu, 28 May 2026 12:36:02 +0200
